"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828095","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-01-25","<p>Recognition as an official Olympic partner is a matter for the International Olympic Committee (IOC). The Government does not therefore set such criteria. Decisions on which sports are on the programmes for the Olympic and Paralympic Games are matters for the IOC and International Paralympic Committee (IPC) respectively. The Deaflympics (previously called World Games for the Deaf and International Games for the Deaf) are an International Olympic Committee (IOC) sanctioned event at which deaf athletes compete at an elite level.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","124056","2018-01-25T15:02:56.52Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828095/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828095/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828095/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-01-22","Olympic Games","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what criteria a sports governing body must fulfil in order to be recognised as an official Olympic partner by the UK Government.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","124055"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828096","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-01-25","<p>Recognition as an official Olympic partner is a matter for the International Olympic Committee (IOC). The Government does not therefore set such criteria. Decisions on which sports are on the programmes for the Olympic and Paralympic Games are matters for the IOC and International Paralympic Committee (IPC) respectively. The Deaflympics (previously called World Games for the Deaf and International Games for the Deaf) are an International Olympic Committee (IOC) sanctioned event at which deaf athletes compete at an elite level.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","124055","2018-01-25T15:02:56.613Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828096/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828096/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828096/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-01-22","Deaflympics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, for what reasons the Deaflympics is not recognised as an official Olympic sporting event by the Government.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","124056"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828097","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-30","<p>Teletracking has been piloted at five Patient and Asset Tracking pilot sites across the National Health Service. These sites had already made the decision locally to implement the Teletracking patient workflow system.</p><p> </p><p>The trusts implementing this system used their own locally driven procurement processes to select providers and as each local trust has agreed the commercial arrangements associated with teletracking independently, information on costs is not centrally available. National funding has not been made available to the pilots.</p><p> </p><p>As the process for selecting providers was undertaken locally by trusts, the assessment of value for money will have formed part of the locally driven procurement processes. The pilot sites have agreed to a set of metrics to be shared with NHS Improvement in order to evaluate impact and inform value for money.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","124050 ; 124052 ; 124058","2018-01-30T14:04:54.557Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828097/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828097/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828097/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-22","TeleTracking Technologies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what is the annual cost to the public purse of each of the five Patient and Asset Tracking pilots being delivered by TeleTracking Technologies is; and what funding is being provided nationally for those pilots.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","124057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828098","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-30","<p>Teletracking has been piloted at five Patient and Asset Tracking pilot sites across the National Health Service. These sites had already made the decision locally to implement the Teletracking patient workflow system.</p><p> </p><p>The trusts implementing this system used their own locally driven procurement processes to select providers and as each local trust has agreed the commercial arrangements associated with teletracking independently, information on costs is not centrally available. National funding has not been made available to the pilots.</p><p> </p><p>As the process for selecting providers was undertaken locally by trusts, the assessment of value for money will have formed part of the locally driven procurement processes. The pilot sites have agreed to a set of metrics to be shared with NHS Improvement in order to evaluate impact and inform value for money.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","124050 ; 124052 ; 124057","2018-01-30T14:04:54.607Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828098/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828098/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828098/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-22","TeleTracking Technologies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what criteria will be used to assess the value for money of the TeleTracking technologies pilots.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","124058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828099","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-30","<p>Many National Health Service trusts are considering implementing Patient Workflow Systems to improve patient flow throughout the hospital and patient pathway. Several trusts already have a patient workflow system in place from various providers. TeleTracking is one of the providers of this technology and has been piloted by four sites across the NHS. Work is underway with NHS Digital to develop a national specification and framework that will simplify the process for providers or Sustainability and Transformation Partnership areas to choose a workflow system to improve patient flow. The intention is to have multiple suppliers on that framework.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-01-30T14:06:27.053Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828099/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828099/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828099/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-22","TeleTracking Technologies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, What plans his Department has to roll out TeleTracking technologies across the NHS.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","124059"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828100","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-01-25","<p>The next edition of UK Statistics on Waste is currently listed with a provisional release date of March 2018 and it is expected that a firm date will be confirmed this month.</p><p> </p><p>The publication date announcement can be found at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/announcements/uk-statistics-on-waste--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/announcements/uk-statistics-on-waste--2</a>.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-01-25T11:37:00.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828100/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828100/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828100/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-01-22","Waste Management","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when his Department plans to release the next edition of UK Statistics on Waste; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","124060"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828101","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-30","<p>Two flights and accommodation for eight nights was provided by TeleTracking to senior staff at NHS Improvement during 2017/18.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-01-30T14:13:01.467Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828101/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828101/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828101/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-22","TeleTracking Technologies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what (a) hospitality, (b) flights and (c) accommodation have been offered by TeleTracking to  senior staff of (i) his Department, (ii) NHS England and (iii) NHS Improvement in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","124061"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828102","Department for Transport","false","2018-01-30","<p>The Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) have advised that the building that currently accommodates Pontypridd driving test centre (DTC) has reached the end of its functional and economic life. The Government-owned Llantrisant goods vehicle testing station (GVTS), which is only seven miles from Pontypridd DTC, provides low-cost alternative accommodation that meets all of the DVSA'S location criteria and testing requirements.</p><p> </p><p>The relocation is expected to reduce the DVSA’s rental liabilities by over £6,000 a year, and avoid significant costs associated with making the current property fit for purpose. The relocation to Llantrisant GVTS should also provide both accommodation and operational efficiency cost savings, while improving the customer experience and maintaining the service quality of the car practical driving test.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-01-30T16:51:44.277Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828102/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828102/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828102/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-22","Driving Tests: Pontypridd","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of the cost of the relocation of Pontypridd driving test centre to Llantrisant.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","124062"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828103","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-30","<p>As TeleTracking systems have been selected and implemented locally, cyber security and technical resilience is a matter for the trust concerned. In producing a national framework with NHS Digital, security and resilience would form part of the specification and shortlisting process.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-01-30T12:02:02.223Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828103/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828103/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828103/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-22","TeleTracking Technologies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the risk of (a) cyber-attacks and (b) technical failure of TeleTracking Technologies' systems used to deliver the Patient and Asset Tracking pilots; and what steps he is taking to mitigate those risks.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","124063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828104","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-30","<p>Through the official receiver, we are continuing to make provision for payments to maintain public services both to suppliers and subcontractors. If any subcontractors are experiencing difficulties they should talk in the first place to the Insolvency Service.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-01-30T15:49:03.257Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828104/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828104/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828104/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-22","Carillion: Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he is taking to ensure that SMEs do not experience delayed payments due to the liquidation of Carillion.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","124064"
