"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828268","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-01-31","<p>There are no Upper Tribunal judgments on Personal Independence Payments dated April 2016 that the Department is currently appealing to the Court of Appeal.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-01-31T11:07:53.537Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828268/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828268/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/828268/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-22","Personal Independence Payment: Tribunals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much was spent by the Government from the public purse in legal fees on seeking to overturn the Upper Tribunal Administrative Appeals Chamber decision of April 2016 on personal independent payments.","false","Biography information for Hugh Gaffney","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Hugh Gaffney","124228"
