"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825724","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-01-25","<p>We received a number of submissions to the Channel 4 regional consultation from individuals and local authorities across the UK. No decisions have been taken. The government is working with Channel 4 on how it can best increase its regional impact, and we will set out next steps in due course.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","124029","2018-01-25T14:55:12.833Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825724/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825724/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825724/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-01-19","Channel Four Television: Location","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what recent discussions he has had with (a) Birmingham City Council and (b) the West Midlands Combined Authority on the potential relocation of Channel 4 outside London.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","123791"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825725","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-01-29","<p>This government is committed to spreading jobs and prosperity throughout the UK, and it is important that our broadcasting sector provides for and reflects the whole country. As part of this, we have made clear that Channel 4 must make a greater regional impact. We are in discussions with Channel 4 about how they should do this, and we will set out next steps soon.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-01-29T17:42:07.393Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825725/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825725/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825725/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-01-19","Broadcasting: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what steps his Department is taking to promote regional diversity in broadcasting.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","123792"
