"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825754","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-29","I refer the Honourable Member to the answer I gave on 22 December 2017 to the Honourable Member for Tottenham (PQ119871) and to the answer I gave on 25 January 2017 to the Honourable Member for Hull North (123405).","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","123816 ; 123817 ; 123818 ; 123820","2018-01-29T14:49:50.587Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825754/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825754/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825754/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-19","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to ensure that families with one working parent that were previously in receipt of childcare vouchers do not face financial hardship as a result of the removal of their entitlement under the new tax-free childcare scheme.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","123821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825755","Department for Education","false","2018-01-29","<p>By 2019-20, the government will be spending around £6 billion a year on childcare support, including £1 billion to deliver 30 hours of free childcare and pay the higher funding rates that we introduced in April 2017.</p><p> </p><p>Our funding rates are based on evidence from our “Review of Childcare Costs”, which was described as “thorough and wide ranging” by the National Audit Office. Local authorities’ individual funding rates are set by the new early years national funding formula which takes account of relative children’s needs and costs of delivery.</p><p> </p><p>Through ‘Childcare Works’, we are supporting all local authorities to deliver 30 hours of free childcare, and we are monitoring carefully its implementation.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","123752","2018-01-29T17:46:31.19Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825755/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825755/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825755/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-19","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if he will ensure that the level of Government funding provided to (a) Liverpool City Council and (b) Knowsley Metropolitan Borough Council is sufficient to allow those local authorities to support the mandatory provision of 30 hours of free childcare for three and four-year-olds.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","123822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825756","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-01-25","<p>This data is not recorded or stored. Candidates taking up appointment into the Civil Service are required to be impartial and independent of political and other external influence.</p><p> </p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-01-25T14:12:24.28Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825756/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825756/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825756/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-19","Department for Work and Pensions: Former Members","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many former Conservative Members of Parliament who were defeated at the 2017 general election and who now work in her Department were appointed after a publicly advertised and open recruitment process.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","123823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825757","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-29","<p>The Department does not hold central information on the former roles of any its employees or their declared political interests. All recruitment within the Department is conducted in line with the Civil Service Commissioner’s recruitment principles and all civil servants adhere to the Civil Service code.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-01-29T12:36:15.26Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825757/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825757/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825757/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-19","Department of Health and Social Care: Former Members","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many former Conservative Members of Parliament who were defeated at the 2017 general election and who now work in his Department were appointed after a publicly advertised and open recruitment process.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","123824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825758","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-30","<p>Records held by the Ministry of Defence indicate that no former Conservative Members of Parliament who were defeated in the General Election of 2017 are currently employed as members of the Senior Civil Service (SCS). Information on the previous employment history of Civil Servants below SCS is not held in the format requested.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-01-30T15:02:15.637Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825758/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825758/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825758/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-19","Ministry of Defence: Former Members","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many former Conservative Members of Parliament who were defeated at the 2017 general election and who now work in his Department were appointed after a publicly advertised and open recruitment process.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","123825"
