,"Bury North","James Frith","123628"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825490","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-01-23","<p>The Judicial Pensions (Fee-Paid Judges) Regulations (the 2017 Regulations) established the Fee-Paid Judicial Pension Scheme on 1 April 2017. We are proposing to amend the 2017 Regulations to clarify the periods for which specified judicial office holders are eligible to receive a pension.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-01-23T17:38:18.85Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825490/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825490/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825490/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-18","Judiciary: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of the proposed changes to part-time judicial pensions.","false","Biography information for Matt Western","Warwick and Leamington","Matt Western","123629"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825491","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-25","<p>Information is not held centrally on the number of dentists who qualified overseas who are waiting for a Performer Number or on the average turnaround time for applications to join the National Dental Performers List.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-01-25T13:47:20.947Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825491/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825491/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825491/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-18","Dentistry: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many overseas qualified dentists are waiting for a Performer Number by country of origin; and what the the average waiting time has been to receive such a number in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for James Frith","Bury North","James Frith","123630"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825492","Department for Education","false","2018-01-23","<p>There are currently seven Partners in Practice. These authorities are: Achieving for Children (Richmond and Kingston), Hampshire, Islington, Lincolnshire, Leeds, North Yorkshire, and Triborough (Westminster, Kensington and Chelsea, and Hammersmith and Fulham). The Department for Education has invested £47 million into these seven Partners in Practice from 2016-20.</p><p> </p><p>Additionally, ministers have committed up to £20 million for improvement work for children’s social care for 2018-20. A proportion of this funding will fund the expansion of the programme with more local authorities joining the Partners in Practice programme from April 2018.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-01-23T17:30:26.007Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825492/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825492/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825492/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-18","Children: Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much money his Department has allocated to the Partners in Practice programme.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","123631"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825493","Department for International Trade","false","2018-01-23","<p>The Government’s objective in any trade negotiations will be to support the best possible outcome for the UK economy as a whole.</p><p>The EU withdrawal bill will transfer into domestic law the EU schemes that currently protect our Geographic Indications (GIs).</p><p>Future protection for current UK GIs in EU Member States, and for GIs in the UK, is subject to negotiations with the EU.</p><p>Some of the GI designations that the UK has, for instance protecting Scotch whisky in the US, are governed by agreements outside the EU Protected Food Name Scheme.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-01-23T15:03:27.997Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825493/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825493/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825493/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-01-18","Food: Origin Marking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what plans he has for recognising protected food names in future trade agreements after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","123632"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825494","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-11-26","<p>There was an underestimation of the historical costs of maintenance and services, which meant that more of the award has been spent on maintenance and services rather than efficiency savings. As a result, the contract has not delivered the anticipated savings.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-11-26T17:48:03.937Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825494/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825494/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825494/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-18","Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what savings his Department has made through its contract with Carillion compared with the projected cost of continuing to provide maintenance in-house in each year since 2015.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","123633"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825495","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-01","<p>The original business case identified potential savings of c.£21m per annum in total, across both the Amey and Carillion contracts, the MITIE contract was in place at time of the business case.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-03-01T18:31:10.463Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825495/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825495/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825495/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-18","Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what savings his Department planned to make through the contract with Carillion compared with the projected cost of continuing to provide maintenance in-house in each year since 2015.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","123634"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825496","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-01","<p>Given the recent liquidation of Carillion it is too early give an estimate of the cost of providing prison maintenance in each of the next 3 years.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-03-01T18:31:20.807Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825496/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825496/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825496/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-18","Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to the liquidation of Carillion, what estimate his Department has made of the cost of providing prison maintenance in each of the next three years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","123635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825497","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-01","<p>HMPPS are expecting to spend £121.8m on prison maintenance in 2017-18, this would be the total expenditure across the three facilities management contracts covering Carillion, Amey and Mitie for fixed and variable costs . This prison maintenance spend includes costs for soft services such as landscaping, cleaning and the provision of stores facilities, depending on the scope of the contracts at individual sites.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-03-01T18:32:28.703Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825497/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825497/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825497/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-01-18","Prisons: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, with reference to the liquidation of Carillion, how much his Department is spending on prison maintenance.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","123636"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825498","Wales Office","false","2018-01-23","<p>The UK Government is committed to reducing emissions across the nation’s transport network. The bi-mode Intercity Express trains on the Great Western route will utilise modern technology and will produce less emissions than today. Once the Great Western transformation is complete the new trains will spend most of the journey between London and Swansea in electric mode, with near-zero emissions. In diesel mode the new trains meet the highest rolling stock emissions standards and will convert nitrogen oxides in exhaust gases into water.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2018-01-23T12:39:03.313Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825498/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825498/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825498/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-01-18","South Wales Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what assessment his Department has made of the environmental effect of not proceeding with the electrification of the Cardiff-Swansea mainline.","false","Biography information for Christina Rees","Neath","Christina Rees","123637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825499","Department for International Development","false","2018-01-22","<p>It is for other governments to decide what percentage of gross national income (GNI) they will allocate as Official Development Assistance (ODA), however in her engagement with international partners the Secretary of State will highlight the importance the UK Government places on meeting the UN target to spend 0.7% of GNI as ODA.</p><p>She will also make clear, as outlined in the UK Aid Strategy, the vital role that international development activity plays in tackling global challenges which threaten the security and prosperity of donors, such as mass migration, climate change and disease, as well as meeting our moral obligation to help the world’s poorest and most vulnerable.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-01-22T17:47:41.917Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825499/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825499/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825499/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-01-18","Development Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will discuss with her foreign counterparts steps to encourage developed countries to meet the UN's 0.7 per cent ODA target.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","123638"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825500","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-01-26","<p>In October 2017, Foreign and Commonwealth officials attended a briefing given by the authors of the report commissioned by the German parliament on Antisemitism. On 18 January, the German parliament voted to establish the position of Antisemitism Commissioner, which is the first recommendation of the report. We continue to cooperate with Germany in international work to combat antisemitism.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-01-26T13:30:21.783Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825500/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825500/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825500/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-01-18","Germany: Antisemitism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions (a) Ministers and (b) officials of his Department have had with their German counterparts on antisemitism and on implementing the conclusions of the recent report by the Second Independent Expert Group on Antisemitism.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","123639"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825501","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-02-07","<p>In 2018, more departments than ever before held events to commemorate Holocaust Memorial Day. These include:</p><ul><li>Department for Business, Energy &amp; Industrial Strategy</li><li>Cabinet Office</li><li>Ministry of Defence</li><li>Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport</li><li>Department for Education</li><li>Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs</li><li>Department for Exiting the European Union</li><li>Foreign and Commonwealth Office</li><li>Home Office</li><li>Department of Health and Social Care</li><li>Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government</li><li>Department for International Development</li><li>Department for International Trade</li><li>Ministry of Justice</li><li>Northern Ireland Office</li><li>Department for Transport</li><li>HM Treasury</li></ul><p> </p><p>Officials in all other departments have been invited to attend these events, or given opportunities to view them remotely. A number of non-Ministerial departments have also held events or their staff have been able to attend those held at Ministerial departments; these include (but are not limited to) the Government Legal Department, the Crown Prosecution Service and the Charity Commission.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-02-07T10:32:42.873Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825501/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825501/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825501/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-18","Holocaust Memorial Day","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, which Departments have (a) marked and (b) plans to mark Holocaust Memorial Day 2018.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","123640"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825502","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-26","<p>A decision on whether to refuel HMS Victorious is to be made later this year and therefore estimated costs related to the refuelling operations have yet to be finalised.</p><p>There are currently no plans to refuel HMS Vigilant or HMS Vengeance.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","123645 ; 123646","2018-01-26T12:08:22.653Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825502/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825502/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825502/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-18","Warships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when a decision will be reached on whether it is necessary to refuel the (a) HMS Victorious, (b) HMS Vigilant and (c) HMS Vengeance.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","123641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825503","Department for International Development","false","2018-01-23","<p>The Prosperity Fund, which is led and managed by the National Security Secretariat in Cabinet Office, is committed to meeting the government target of ‘good’ on the International Aid Transparency Index by 2020. The Fund is working closely with DFID policy and Transparency teams, benefiting from their experience and expertise and the International Aid Transparency Initiative to ensure it meets standards for transparency.</p><p>The Fund has already begun working towards this target, publishing its first Annual Review in 2017, alongside a data release on spend for 2016/17. It will continue to increase the amount of information published on spend and programmes as it becomes available.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-01-23T17:39:26.187Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825503/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825503/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825503/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-01-18","Prosperity Fund: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, with reference to paragraph 4.11 of UK aid: tackling global challenges in the national interest, published in November 2015, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that the transparency standards of the Prosperity Fund are ranked as good or very good in the international Aid Transparency Index.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","123642"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825504","Department for International Development","false","2018-01-23","<p>The Prosperity Fund is committed to meeting the government target of ‘good’ on the International Aid Transparency Index by 2020. The Fund was announced in the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review; no further allocations have been made beyond the initial £1.2bn allocated over the Fund’s six year lifetime. The Fund is managed and led by the National Security Secretariat in Cabinet Office. Any future funding would be agreed across government following the appropriate procedures.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-01-23T17:31:47.663Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825504/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825504/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825504/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-01-18","Prosperity Fund: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will make it her policy that there there will be no further increases in spending from the Prosperity Fund until that fund is ranked good or very good in the International Aid Transparency Index.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","123643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825505","Cabinet Office","false","2018-03-06","<p>The publication of the first annual report of the Prosperity Fund was on 1<sup>st</sup> December 2017, and approved by the then First Secretary of State. The report was laid before Parliament by the Minister for the Constitution, Chris Skidmore in a Written Ministerial Statement on 21 December.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2018-03-06T16:36:40.68Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825505/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825505/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825505/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-18","Prosperity Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which Secretary of State had responsibility for the publication of the first annual report of the Prosperity Fund.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","123644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825506","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-26","<p>A decision on whether to refuel HMS Victorious is to be made later this year and therefore estimated costs related to the refuelling operations have yet to be finalised.</p><p>There are currently no plans to refuel HMS Vigilant or HMS Vengeance.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","123641 ; 123646","2018-01-26T12:08:22.713Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825506/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825506/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825506/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-18","Trident Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the potential cost of the Vanguard-class submarine refuelling operations.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","123645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825507","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-26","<p>A decision on whether to refuel HMS Victorious is to be made later this year and therefore estimated costs related to the refuelling operations have yet to be finalised.</p><p>There are currently no plans to refuel HMS Vigilant or HMS Vengeance.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","123641 ; 123645","2018-01-26T12:08:22.76Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825507/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825507/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825507/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-18","Trident Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate his Department has made of the potential cost to (a) Devonport Royal Dockyard, (b) Rolls Royce in Derby and (c) elsewhere for refuelling operations to extend the lifespan of the Vanguard-class submarines until the Dreadnought submarines are built.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","123646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825509","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-01-25","<p>Littering is a concern for everyone, residents and visitors alike. VisitBritain have recently carried out research into the factors that encourage people to come to the UK. Litter was one of the factors they asked people to consider, and the report will be released on the VisitBritain website in due course.</p><p> </p><p>Additionally, the Department of Environment, Food and Rural Affairs have put forward measures in their 25 Year Plan to address littering.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"2018-01-25T12:31:10.403Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825509/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825509/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825509/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-01-18","Tourism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether he has held recent discussions with Cabinet colleagues on the effect on levels of tourism of litter on (a) public highways and (b) the countryside; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Lefroy","Stafford","Jeremy Lefroy","123647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825510","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-25","<p>The Industrial Strategy white paper sets out a long-term plan to boost the productivity and earning power of people throughout the UK. Through the Clean Growth Grand Challenge we will maximise the advantages for UK industry from the global shift to clean growth. The upcoming UK Bioeconomy Strategy will build on these themes to set out a framework for growth for companies within the bioeconomy, including those working in the bioenergy sector.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-01-25T11:40:10.093Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825510/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825510/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825510/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-18","Biofuels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps his Department plans to take to encourage the development of (a) SMEs and (b) other businesses in the bio-energy Industry.","true","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","123648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825511","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-23","<p>I refer the honourable member to the answer that I gave on 12 January to PQ UIN 121049.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen","123651","2018-01-23T11:38:43.513Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825511/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825511/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825511/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-18","Royal Bank of Scotland: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans (a) Ministers and (b) officials of his Department have to meet with representatives of UK Financial Investments to discuss the closures of Royal Bank of Scotland branches in (i) Scotland and (ii) Midlothian constituency.","false","Biography information for Danielle Rowley","Midlothian","Danielle Rowley","123649"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825512","Department for International Development","false","2018-01-23","<p>Secretary of State for International Development spoke to Mme Audrey Azoulay, UNESCO Director General, within two weeks of being appointed as Secretary of State. Mme Azoulay assured Secretary of State of the seriousness with which she is approaching the task of reforming UNESCO and confirmed her willingness to work with the UK on this. The Secretary of State has also written to Mme Azoulay outlining UK priorities for UNESCO reform, based on the 2017 performance improvement plan.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-01-23T17:35:17.143Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825512/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825512/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/825512/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-01-18","UNESCO: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what recent discussions she has had with UNESCO on progress with its performance improvement plan.","false","Biography information for Stephen Twigg","Liverpool, West Derby","Stephen Twigg","123650"
